%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22OTT%20Networks%2C%20Film%20Makers%20Under%20Direct%20and%20Indirect%20Control%20of%20Union%20Govt%2C%20BJP%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F21142605%2FUntitled-design-2-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%20The%20Washington%20Post%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2F11%2F20%2Findia-netflix-amazon-movies-self-censorship%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ein%20an%20investigation%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20behind%20the%20scenes%20goings%20on%20at%20India%20commissioning%20decisions%20of%20big%20streaming%20giants%20from%20the%20US%2C%20Amazon%E2%80%99s%20Prime%20Video%20and%20Netflix%2C%20concludes%20that%20%E2%80%9Cjust%20as%20the%20BJP%20and%20its%20ideological%20allies%20have%20spread%20propaganda%20on%20WhatsApp%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2F09%2F26%2Fhindu-nationalist-social-media-hate-campaign%2F%3Fitid%3Dlk_inline_manual_5%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eto%20advance%20their%20Hindu-first%20agenda%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0and%20deployed%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20coercive%20muscle%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2F11%2F08%2Findia-twitter-online-censorship%2F%3Fitid%3Dlk_inline_manual_5%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eto%20squash%20dissent%20on%20Twitter%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0they%20have%20used%20the%20threat%20of%20criminal%20cases%20and%20coordinated%20mass%20public%20pressure%20to%20shape%20what%20Indian%20content%20gets%20produced%20by%20Netflix%20and%20Prime%20Video.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20newspaper%20has%20spoken%20of%20how%20the%20%E2%80%9Cculture%20of%20self-censorship%20pervades%20the%20streaming%20industry%20here%2C%20manifesting%20in%20ways%20both%20dramatic%20and%20subtle.%20Executives%20at%20the%20India%20offices%20of%20Netflix%20and%20Prime%20Video%20and%20their%20lawyers%20ask%20for%20extensive%20changes%20to%20rework%20political%20plots%20and%20remove%20passing%20references%20to%20religion%20that%20might%20offend%20the%20Hindu%20right%20wing%20or%20the%20BJP%2C%20industry%20insiders%20say.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20investigation%20zeroes%20in%20on%20how%20%E2%80%9Cprojects%20that%20deal%20with%20India%E2%80%99s%20political%2C%20religious%20or%20caste%20divisions%20are%20politely%20declined%20when%20they%20are%20proposed%2C%20or%20dropped%20midway%20through%20development.%20Even%20completed%20series%20and%20films%20have%20been%20quietly%20abandoned%20and%20withheld%20by%20Netflix%20and%20Prime%20Video%20from%20their%20viewers%20worldwide.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFilm%20director%2C%20Anurag%20Kashyap%20has%20termed%20the%20results%20as%20being%20akin%20to%20that%20under%20an%20%E2%80%9Cinvisible%20censorship%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%E2%80%98Self-censorship%E2%80%99%20Plus%20Plus%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20newspaper%20dates%20back%20the%20impact%20of%20methods%20involving%20outrage%2C%20restrictive%20government%20rules%20and%20threats%20of%20the%20police%20to%20what%20happened%20with%20the%20series%2C%20Tandav%2C%20a%20Prime%20Video%20production%2C%20which%20it%20describes%20as%20%E2%80%9Ca%20watershed%20moment.%E2%80%9D%20An%20employee%20of%20the%20streaming%20giant%20here%20%E2%80%9Cwas%20forced%20to%20briefly%20go%20into%20hiding%20and%20surrender%20her%20passport%20to%20police%2C%20according%20to%20people%20familiar%20with%20the%20matter%E2%80%9D%2C%20as%20per%20the%20report.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EParth%20Arora%2C%20a%20former%20director%20of%20production%20management%20for%20Netflix%20India%20told%20The%20Washington%20Post%2C%20%E2%80%9CYou%20wanted%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20you%20are%20not%20making%20the%20same%20mistakes%20that%20happened%20on%20%E2%80%98Tandav.%E2%80%9D%20He%20added%2C%20that%20companies%20%E2%80%9Chad%20to%20review%20the%20projects%20going%20forward.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMany%20projects%20greenlit%20and%20also%20shot%20were%20not%20used%2C%20including%20one%20series%20called%20%E2%80%98Gormint%E2%80%99%20that%20has%20commentary%20on%20the%20state%20of%20the%20government%20and%20is%20critical%20of%20Indian%20politics%2C%20what%20The%20Washington%20Post%20terms%2C%20%E2%80%9Ca%20satirical%20series%20billed%20as%20India%E2%80%99s%20answer%20to%20%E2%80%9CVeep%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202021%2C%20Anurag%20Kashyap%20told%20The%20Washington%20Post%2C%20in%202021%2C%20Netflix%20shelved%20an%20adaptation%20of%20the%20nonfiction%20book%20Maximum%20City%2C%20%E2%80%9Cwhich%20explores%20Hindu%20bigotry%20and%20the%20extremes%20of%20hope%20and%20despair%20in%20Mumbai.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20early%202021%2C%20says%20the%20newspaper%2C%20the%20first%20bid%20to%20control%20OTT%20platforms%20was%20made%20when%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20Indian%20government%20introduced%20a%20system%20of%20self-regulation%20in%20which%20streaming%20companies%20must%20resolve%20viewer%20complaints%20within%2015%20days%2C%20or%20else%20face%20regulatory%20scrutiny%20by%20an%20industry%20body%20or%20a%20government%20committee%20staffed%20by%20various%20ministries.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20the%20Numbers%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndustry%20insiders%20plead%20economics%2C%20which%20is%20allowing%20the%20current%20government%20to%20instil%20a%20chilling%20effect%2C%20self-censorship%20as%20well%20as%20direction%20from%20streaming%20giants%20to%20creators%20to%20not%20be%20candid.%20Streaming%20revenues%20in%20India%20are%20projected%20to%20grow%20from%20%242.6%20billion%20in%202022%20to%20%2413%20billion%20in%202030%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Confederation%20of%20Indian%20Industry%20(CII)%20and%20the%20Boston%20Consulting%20Group.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EDeploying%20Mobs%20for%20Politics%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20viewer%20%E2%80%98outrage%E2%80%99%20and%20its%20deployment%20for%20larger%20political%20goals%20is%20explained%20via%20the%20case%20of%20Tandav.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERamesh%20Solanki%2C%20was%20the%20right-wing%20petitioner%20who%20filed%20the%20first%20police%20complaint%20against%20the%20series%20in%202019.%20In%20an%20interview%20to%20the%20newspaper%2C%20Solanki%20described%20the%20existence%20of%20%E2%80%9Chundreds%E2%80%9D%20of%20WhatsApp%20and%20Facebook%20groups%20where%20Hindu%20nationalists%20like%20himself%20had%20gathered%20%E2%80%9Cto%20discuss%20how%20to%20apply%20pressure%20on%20streaming%20platforms.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20groups%E2%80%99%20members%20were%20scattered%20worldwide%2C%20he%20recalled%2C%20and%20offered%20financial%20and%20legal%20aid%20to%20those%20who%20volunteered%20to%20file%20complaints%20against%20the%20foreign%20companies.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESolanki%20said%2C%20he%20was%20flooded%20with%20congratulatory%20messages%20from%20BJP%20leaders%20and%2C%20in%202022%2C%20joined%20the%20BJP.%20He%20boasts%20to%20the%20newspaper%2C%20that%20Prime%20Video%20and%20Netflix%20have%20learned%20their%20lesson%2C%20%E2%80%9CThey%20are%20aware%3A%20If%20we%20do%20any%20mischief%2C%20if%20we%20cross%20the%20line%2C%20we%20will%20face%20the%20music.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CYou%20self-censor%20stuff%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20director%20told%20The%20Washington%20Post.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20a%20gun%20to%20your%20head%20because%20at%20any%20point%20of%20time%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20so%20easy%20to%20mobilise%20a%20bunch%20of%20people.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENew%20Controversial%20Draft%20Broadcasting%20Bill%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20new%20controversial%20draft%20broadcasting%20services%20(regulation)%20bill%2C%202023%2C%20set%20to%20replace%20the%20Cable%20Television%20Networks%20(Regulation)%20Act%20legislated%20in%201995%2C%20now%20wants%20to%20be%20able%20to%20regulate%20the%20entire%20media%20space%20which%20has%20exploded%20with%20the%20advent%20of%20the%20internet%20offering%20direct%20broadcast%20options%20as%20well%20as%20social%20media%20and%20the%20prevalence%20of%20relatively%20cheap%20broadband.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20draft%20has%20been%20criticised%20by%20senior%20media%20scholar%20Sevanti%20Ninan%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Fopinion%2Fnew-talons-indias-content-regulatory-regime-is-flourishing%2Fcid%2F1981090%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ein%20a%20piece%20titled%20New%20Talons%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20particularly%20for%20its%20%E2%80%98three-tier%20regulatory%20framework%E2%80%99.%20Ninan%20writes%20of%20the%20heavy%20handedness%20proposed%2C%20all%20the%20while%20preferring%20to%20call%20it%20a%20%E2%80%98light%20touch%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%20%E2%80%9CNeither%20broadcasters%20nor%20OTT%20operators%20think%20the%20three-tier%20regulatory%20mechanism%20proposed%20in%20the%20new%20bill%20is%20a%20%E2%80%98light%20touch%E2%80%99.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20is%20worse%2C%20%E2%80%9CIndia%20is%20going%20to%20be%20one%20of%20the%20few%20democracies%20in%20the%20world%20which%20require%20broadcasters%20to%20set%20up%20content%20evaluation%20committees%20to%20certify%20programmes%20that%20should%20be%20broadcast.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EReplacing%20the%20nine-page%20bill%20of%20the%20past%20with%20a%2072-page%20bill%20has%20been%20viewed%20with%20dismay%20with%20digital%20rights%20groups%20too%2C%20as%20leaving%20far%20too%20much%20in%20the%20sphere%20of%20government%20discretion.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finternetfreedom.in%2Fbroadcast-services-bill-first-read%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Internet%20Freedom%20Foundation%20notes%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20the%20Bill%20includes%2060%20instances%20of%20%E2%80%9Cas%20may%20be%20prescribed%E2%80%9D%20and%2017%20instances%20of%20%E2%80%9Cas%20notified%20by%20the%20%5BUnion%5D%20Government%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20provision%2C%20calling%20for%20explicit%20seizing%20of%20equipment%20also%20signals%20intentions%20far%20from%20%E2%80%9Clight%20touch%20regulation.%E2%80%9D%20Clause%2031%20allows%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20inspect%2C%20intercept%2C%20monitor%2C%20and%20seize%20the%20equipment%20of%20broadcasting%20networks%20and%20services.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20is%20currently%20at%20161%20of%20180%20countries%20in%20the%20World%20Press%20Freedom%20index%20and%20the%20Swedish%20Sweden%E2%80%99s%20International%20Institute%20for%20Democracy%20and%20Electoral%20Assistance%2C%20or%20International%20IDEA%2C%20studying%20democracies%20for%20decades%20globally%2C%20along%20Global%20State%20of%20Democracy%20Index%20(or%20the%20GSoD)%20that%20it%20measures%2C%20found%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20score%20on%20fundamental%20rights%20in%202010%20was%20low%20at%20.58.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20by%202020%2C%20it%20fell%20further%20to%20.54.%20In%20the%20decade%20between%202010%20and%202020%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20score%20on%20civil%20liberties%20tanked%20from%20.65%20to%20.53.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700557074000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F21142605%2FUntitled-design-2-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fself-censorship-ott-netflix-amazon-prime-hindu-first%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20new%20investigation%20by%20The%20Washington%20Post%20which%20deals%20a%20blow%20to%20the%20%E2%80%98vibrant%20democracy%E2%80%99%20image%20the%20go