k%5C%22%3EMicrosoft%20CEO%20Satya%20Nadella%3C%2Fa%3E%20went%20on%20a%20media%20blitz%20Monday%20afternoon%20speaking%20to%20CNBC%2C%20BloombergTV%2C%20and%20Kara%20Swisher.%20During%20these%20interviews%2C%20he%20offered%20nothing%20but%20praise%20for%20recently%20ousted%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-ousted-fired-openai-ceo-chatgpt-maker-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EOpenAI%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Ebut%20made%20comments%20about%20OpenAI's%20board%20governance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FCNBC%2Fstatus%2F1726744999281254740%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ECNBC%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20%26quot%3Bsomething%20has%20to%20change%26quot%3B%20in%20regards%20to%20the%20board%20of%20directors%2C%20but%20stopped%20short%20of%20saying%20what%20changes%20he%20would%20like%20to%20see%20%E2%80%94%20including%20whether%20or%20not%20Microsoft%20should%20have%20its%20own%20seat%20at%20the%20table.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20at%20this%20point%2C%20I%20think%20it's%20very%2C%20very%20clear%20that%20something%20has%20to%20change%20around%20the%20governance%2C%20and%20we'll%20have%20a%20good%20dialogue%20with%20their%20board%20on%20that%20and%20we'll%20walk%20through%20that%20as%20time%20evolves%2C%26quot%3B%20Nadella%20told%20CNBC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENadella%20reiterated%20his%20point%20in%20a%20later%20interview%20with%20BloombergTV%2C%20saying%20that%20%26quot%3Bsurprises%20are%20bad%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20they%20hoped%20to%20prevent%20them%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20just%20want%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20things%20are%20done%20in%20a%20way%20that%20will%20allow%20us%20to%20continue%20to%20partner%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20Nadella%20told%20the%20outlet.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20about%20it.%20This%20idea%20that%20somehow%2C%20sudden%20changes%20happen%20without%20being%20in%20the%20loop%20is%20not%20good.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20with%20tech%20journalist%20Kara%20Swisher%2C%20on%20her%20podcast%20%26quot%3BOn%20With%20Kara%20Swisher%2C%26quot%3B%20Nadella%20hinted%20that%20a%20board%20seat%20or%20observer%20for%20Microsoft%20at%20OpenAI%20was%20a%20possibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe'll%20sort%20of%20cross%20that%20if%20it%20happens%2C%20but%20I%20think%20that%20we%20will%20need%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20our%20interests%20are%20solid%2C%26quot%3B%20Nadella%20told%20Swisher%20in%20response%20to%20a%20question%20about%20a%20board%20seat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENadella%20also%20said%20that%20he%20did%20not%20have%20an%20opinion%20on%20whether%20the%20current%20board%20should%20remain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENadella%20told%20Swisher%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethat%20he%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-ceo-satya-nadella-sam-altman-openai-ousted-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblindsided%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20Friday%20ousting%20of%20Altman%20by%20the%20board%20of%20directors.%20The%20board%20said%20that%20Altman%20was%20%26quot%3Bnot%20consistently%20candid%20in%20his%20communications%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20it%20lacked%20%26quot%3Bconfidence%26quot%3B%20in%20Altman's%20ability%20to%20lead%20the%20company.%20The%20company%20did%20not%20go%20into%20further%20detail.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENadella%20told%20Bloomberg%20TV%20that%20he%20is%20still%20unaware%20of%20why%20exactly%20the%20board%20dumped%20Altman.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20not%20been%20told%20about%20anything%2C%26quot%3B%20Nadella%20told%20Bloomberg%20TV%20Monday.%20%26quot%3BThey%20published%20internally%20at%20OpenAI%20that%20the%20board%20has%20not%20talked%20about%20anything%20that%20Sam%20did%20other%20than%20some%20breakdown%20in%20communications.%20I%20not%20directly%20was%20told%20by%20anyone%20from%20their%20board%20about%20any%20issues%2C%20and%20so%20therefore%20I%20remain%20confident%20in%20Sam%20and%20his%20leadership%20and%20capability.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20now%2C%20Microsoft%20has%20expressed%20interest%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-has-hired-former-openai-ceo-sam-altman-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehiring%20Altman%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20former%20OpenAI%20president%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-president-greg-brockman-quits-sam-altman-ceo-ousted-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EGreg%20Brockman%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20Nadella%20told%20BloombergTV%20that%20their%20hiring%20wasn't%20a%20done%20deal%20and%20that%20they%20were%20%26quot%3Bin%20the%20process%20of%20joining.%26quot%3B%20Nadella%2C%20however%2C%20also%20said%20that%20he%20would%20continue%20to%20work%20with%20Altman%20and%20OpenAI%20regardless%20of%20how%20things%20shook%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-workers-threaten-to-quit-over-sam-altman-firing-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EAltman's%20sudden%20departure%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20created%20shockwaves%20throughout%20the%20AI%20sphere%20and%20hundreds%20of%20OpenAI%20employees%20threatened%20to%20leave%20the%20company%20if%20the%20reins%20were%20not%20handed%20back%20to%20Altman%20(Nadella%20also%20offered%20these%20employees%20jobs%20at%20Microsoft).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-openai-investors-ceo-board-chatgpt-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EOpenAI%20investors%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20also%20reportedly%20gotten%20involved%20in%20trying%20to%20get%20Altman%20back%20to%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20a%20concrete%20reason%20for%20his%20ouster%20has%20yet%20to%20be%20given%2C%20the%20tech%20world%20has%20been%20flooded%20with%20rumors.%20Two%20employees%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenais-e