mer%20who%20owns%20three%20acre%20farmland%20on%20which%20he%20grows%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ELohini%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20an%20indigenous%20variety%20of%20paddy%20without%20using%20chemical%20fertilisers%2C%20recounted%20a%20number%20of%20diverse%20paddy%20varieties%20which%20the%20farmers%20grew%20locally%20and%20compared%20the%20appearance%20of%20fortified%20rice%20kernels%20to%20%E2%80%93%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EBhajna%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ELusdi%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EKhandsagar%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20paddy%20varieties.%20Kulu%2C%20who%20has%20three%20family%20members%2C%20got%2020%20kilos%20of%20rice%20from%20the%20ration%20shop%20every%20month.%20Since%20January%2C%20he%20had%20been%20receiving%20fortified%20rice%20kernels%20in%20food%20rations%2C%20which%20he%20separated%20out.%20%E2%80%9CYou%20can%20easily%20spot%20the%20differences%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Kulu.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20sort%20it%20out%20and%20give%20it%20to%20the%20hens.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20East%20Singhbhum%E2%80%99s%20Chakulia%2C%20which%20was%20part%20of%20the%20pilot%20in%20Jharkhand%2C%20even%20after%20a%20year%2C%20women%20rice%20farmers%20said%20they%20did%20not%20trust%20the%20new%20fortified%20grains.%20Phulmani%20Soren%E2%80%99s%20family%20who%20farm%20in%20Digih%20village%20on%20the%20edge%20of%20Chakulia%20town%20get%2015%20kg%20rice%20every%20month%20as%20food%20rations.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20do%20not%20eat%20the%20new%20grains%2C%20because%20it%20is%20plastic%20rice.%E2%80%9D%20She%20said%20this%20was%20even%20after%20the%20local%20village%20health%20worker%20had%20told%20them%20that%20the%20new%20rice%20was%20a%20kind%20of%20%E2%80%9Cvitamin%20rice%E2%80%9D.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20looks%20distinct%20from%20rice%2C%20and%20it%20separates%20from%20rice%20when%20we%20cook%20it.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E