e%20incident%20occurred%20in%20the%20Kangchup%20area.%20Kuki-Zo%20village%20volunteers%2C%20patrolling%20the%20road%20between%20Leilon%20Vaiphei%20village%20and%20Kharam%20Vaiphei%20village%2C%20were%20allegedly%20ambushed%20by%20Meitei%20insurgents%20wearing%20state%20commandos%E2%80%99%20uniforms.%20This%20case%20bears%20resemblance%20to%20a%20previous%20ambush%20in%20the%20Kangchup%20area%2C%20where%20three%20volunteers%20were%20killed%20allegedly%20by%20disguised%20Meitei%20militants%20on%20September%2012.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResponding%20to%20the%20escalating%20violence%2C%20COTU%20called%20for%20an%20emergency%20meeting%20on%20Monday%2C%20advocating%20for%20a%20shutdown%20in%20Kangpokpi%20district.%20According%20to%20COTU%2C%20the%20group%20responsible%20for%20the%20killings%20is%20the%20same%20group%20of%20disguised%20insurgents%20operating%20in%20Moreh%2C%20a%20border%20town%20in%20Tengnoupal%20district.%20COTU%20reported%20various%20alleged%20atrocities%20committed%20by%20this%20group%2C%20including%20looting%20church%20funds%2C%20burning%20vehicles%2C%20harassing%20women%20and%20children%2C%20and%20demolishing%20houses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20Manipur%20police%20officer%20overseeing%20the%20construction%20of%20a%20helipad%20in%20Moreh%20was%20shot%20dead%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20October%2031%2C%20by%20suspected%20militants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indigenous%20Tribal%20Leaders%E2%80%99%20Forum%20(ITLF)%20said%20that%20the%20deceased%20killed%20in%20the%20recent%20violence%20were%20repairing%20the%20Lamka-Kangpokpi%20road%2C%20damaged%20by%20the%20recent%20spell%20of%20rainfall.%20After%20dropping%20off%20their%20friends%20at%20a%20designated%20point%2C%20they%20were%20ambushed%20while%20attempting%20to%20return%20to%20Leimakhong%2C%20a%20mere%2050%20metres%20from%20where%20they%20left%20their%20friends.%20Since%20the%20victims%20and%20their%20friends%20were%20unarmed%2C%20they%20were%20unable%20to%20defend%20themselves.%20One%20of%20the%20deceased%2C%20Henmin